======================================================================
PART 2: IS prod(1+Q_k) SCHUR-CONVEX?
======================================================================

f(Q) is Schur-convex if Q majorizes Q' => f(Q) >= f(Q').
Schur-convexity of prod(1+Q_k) would mean: the more
concentrated the Q-spectrum, the larger the product.

Test: Does Q_Interval majorize Q_Paley?

  p=7:
    Q_Int sorted desc: [5.04891734 0.64310413 0.30797853]
    Q_Pal sorted desc: [2. 2. 2.]
    Interval majorizes Paley? True
    Paley majorizes Interval? False
    prod(1+Q_Int) = 13.0000
    prod(1+Q_Pal) = 27.0000

  p=11:
    Q_Int sorted desc: [12.34353752  1.44869057  0.5829645   0.35325328  0.27155413]
    Q_Pal sorted desc: [3. 3. 3. 3. 3.]
    Interval majorizes Paley? True
    Paley majorizes Interval? False
    prod(1+Q_Int) = 89.0000
    prod(1+Q_Pal) = 1024.0000

  p=23:
    Q_Int sorted desc: [53.68231728  6.03947168  2.22926959  1.18114046  0.75174361]
    Q_Pal sorted desc: [6. 6. 6. 6. 6.]
    Interval majorizes Paley? True
    Paley majorizes Interval? False
    prod(1+Q_Int) = 28657.0000
