  Q_1/Q_2 grows with p — NOT a universal constant.
  The gap keeps widening, making Interval increasingly dominant.

  Normalized: Q_1/m values:
    p= 7: Q_1/m = 1.682972 (→ m/3 ≈ 1.0000)
    p=11: Q_1/m = 2.468708 (→ m/3 ≈ 1.6667)
